Class TypedHandlerDelegate

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.intellij.codeInsight.editorActions.TypedHandlerDelegate
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    CompletionAutoPopupHandler, GroovyTypedHandler, GStringTypedActionHandler, JavadocTypedHandler, JavaTypedHandler, JsonTypedHandler, MarkdownTypedHandler, PyKeywordTypedHandler, PyMethodNameTypedHandler, PythonConsoleAutopopupBlockingHandler, PythonSpaceHandler, SelectionQuotingTypedHandler, ShTypedHandler, SpaceHandler, StructuralSearchTypedHandler, TextMateTypedHandler, XmlAutoPopupHandler, XmlEqTypedHandler, XmlGtTypedHandler, XmlPiTypedHandler, XmlSlashTypedHandler, XPathTypedHandler, YAMLHyphenTypedHandler

    public abstract class TypedHandlerDelegate
extends java.lang.Object
    Handler, extending IDE behaviour on typing in editor.

    Note that PsiFile passed to handler's methods isn't guaranteed to be in sync with the document at the time of invocation (due to performance considerations). PsiDocumentManager.commitDocument(Document) should be invoked explicitly, if an up-to-date PSI is required.

                                                  Project project,

        If the specified character triggers auto-popup, schedules the auto-popup appearance. This method is called even in overwrite mode, when the rest of typed handler delegate methods are not called. It is invoked only for the primary caret.
